# Trivy ignore file for known vulnerabilities with no available fix.
# Format: CVE-ID or vulnerability ID
#
# Only list findings here when the upstream author has released NO fix
# (trivy reports an empty "Fixed Version"). Anything with a fix version
# must instead be bumped via globalOverrides in
# common/config/rush/pnpm-config.json. Keep entries in sync with the
# submodule's submodules/wso2-vscode-extensions/.trivyignore.

# cors-anywhere@0.4.4 — direct devDependency (local CORS proxy used in dev
# only, never built or shipped). SSRF is inherent to the tool and no fix has
# been released by the author. https://github.com/wso2/vscode-extensions/issues/550
CVE-2020-36851

# elliptic@6.6.1 — transitive dep of the browserify crypto stack
# (create-ecdh / browserify-sign). No fix released by the author; 6.6.1 is
# the latest published version.
CVE-2025-14505
